{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"PLAN REFINEMENT (resolving the two blocking plan-review findings).\n\nRESOLUTION A — structural mismatch (G6). Resolve as option (b)+(a) hybrid: the reusable _build-and-test.yml defines THREE jobs mirroring test.yml's current decomposition — 'lint' (make lint + pre-commit + make typecheck + make config-check), 'pip-audit' (the network-retried scan), and 'test' (the os×py matrix: install .[dev] + git identity + all drift/module-size gates + default suite + integration tier). Each job carries the SAME conditional-checkout pair as _optionality.yml (branch-head via actions/checkout when gerrit-refspec=='' ; checkout-gerrit-change-action on the patchset when set). test.yml KEEPS its job-graph parallelism unchanged because the reusable preserves lint/pip-audit as separate jobs — it simply calls the reusable instead of inlining them. gerrit-verify.yaml's monolithic build-and-test job is REPLACED by a single reusable-call job still named 'build-and-test' (needs: [clear-vote, require-ticket]); this splits gerrit's currently-inline lint/mypy/config-check/pre-commit OUT of the 4x matrix so they run once (a net improvement, not just parity). The union of test.yml's lint+pip-audit+test == gerrit's current build-and-test gate set, so nothing is dropped. golden-path stays duplicated for now (out of scope; noted as a follow-up); the 'external' job stays in test.yml only (needs secrets — the reusable takes NONE).\n\nRESOLUTION B — parity test rewrite (G1G2). test_ci_workflow_parity.py is retargeted from 'grep both caller files for identical command strings' to 'assert both callers delegate to ONE shared source, so drift is impossible by construction' (the same invariant it already asserts for _optionality). Concretely, after extraction:\n - NEW _REUSABLE_BAT = './.github/workflows/_build-and-test.yml'. test_verified_gate_runs_every_shared_gate: assert each _SHARED_GATE_SIGNATURES value appears in _build-and-test.yml (the reusable), AND assert BOTH test.yml and gerrit-verify.yaml contain the string _REUSABLE_BAT (delegation). This proves the gate exists and that both lanes run it via the same file.\n - test_no_drift_script_gate_is_verified_only_in_branch_ci: scan the REUSABLE for scripts/*.py (they now gate both lanes by construction); keep _INTENTIONAL_SCRIPT_ASYMMETRIES empty. The old test.yml-vs-gerrit diff is obsolete once there is a single source.\n - test_branch_sensitive_precommit_hooks_skipped_in_ci and test_ci_redundant_hooks_skipped_in_precommit: point _precommit_all_files_steps at _build-and-test.yml (the reusable now owns the single pre-commit step) and assert the SKIP set there; keep asserting the direct 'make lint'/'make typecheck' steps exist in the reusable.\n - test_optionality_contract_gates_the_verified_path: UNCHANGED (optionality wiring is untouched; vote still lists 'build-and-test, optionality' in needs).\n - test_workflow_names.py: add '_build-and-test.yml' -> 'Build and Test (reusable)' to the locked table so the naming gate covers it.\n\nVALIDATION NOTE: g2p dispatches gerrit-verify.yaml from main's ref, so this change's own Verified run uses the OLD inline gate; the refactored reusable path first executes post-merge via test.yml (branch-head) — watched immediately after landing. actionlint (make lint) validates the reusable 'uses:' wiring + workflow_call input schema locally pre-merge."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784444812545772001,"uuid":"a20c8c23-7793-4c45-a965-249e71730f3f"}